\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. H. atomarium} Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 2}({\b 8}): 114 (1849). Stems 15-75 cm, erect or ascending, not rooting, shortly pubescent. Leaves 15-45(-55) mm, ovate to oblong or elliptical, sessile, shortly pubescent. Inflorescence cylindrical, rarely corymbose, relatively lax, glabrous. Bracts sometimes with long glandular cilia at the base but not auriculate. Sepals black-glandular-denticulate, with superficial black dots. Petals (8-)9-12 mm, sometimes with a few superficial black glands.{\i  Damp, shady places. S. Greece} ({\i Peloponnisos}). Gr. ({\i E. Aegean region, W. Anatolia}.)
